heaviest_rainfall.status: The storm today is ranked 7th for the amount of rainfall recorded during one storm.  22.48mm fell at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour over 28.9 hours.  On 09 November 2025, a record rainfall of 47.89mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  24.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: On 02 September 2025, the rain fell at an exceptional rate, peaking at 34.3mm per hour, the heaviest downpour recorded.  A total of 21.19mm fell over the 15.0 hour storm.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 28.9 hours on 09 November 2025 (ranking 7th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 22.48mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  The lengthiest precipitation event recorded spanned 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025, it was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 24.6mm per hour and a total rainfall of 47.89mm.
